  <!-- the tabs -->
  <div class="border px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:max-w-7xl" data-tabs-target="tab" id="tab-bungarribee">
      <h1 class="text-pretty text-4xl font-medium tracking-tighter text-gray-950 data-[dark]:text-white sm:text-6xl">Bungarribee Park</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-2xl font-medium text-gray-500">Western Sydney Parklands</p>
      <div>
        <div class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-1 gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4">
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-500">January 19</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">April 20</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">July 20</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">October 19</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <section class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="max-w-lg">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Course Start Point</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">The course starts on the Western Sydney Parklands Track, at the western edge of Bungarribee Park. If driving, enter the park at the Eastern Road traffic lights (Blacktown International Sports Park - Area B). The road is called Football Drive on Google Maps or Wumarra Avenue on other mapping platforms. Head through the roundabout and park in the carpark on your left.</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text-lg/6 text-gray-600"><a class="text-[#54494B] underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:no-underline hover:text-[#9DA39A]" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/WS10+-+Bungarribee/@-33.7744756,150.8566326,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x6b129b002d6837c1:0x798780060e2cc67a!8m2!3d-33.7744756!4d150.8580711!16s%2Fg%2F11wx_41zpq?authuser=1&entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDEwMS4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D">Google Maps Link</a> | <a class="text-[#54494B] underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:no-underline hover:text-[#9DA39A]" href="https://maps.apple.com/?ll=-33.774452,150.858074&q=WS10%20-%20Bungarribee">Apple Maps Link</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:row-span-2 mt-8 lg:my-auto">
          <%= image_tag "bungarribee-start.png", class: "rounded-lg" %>
        </div>
        <div class="max-lg:mt-8 lg:col-span-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Facilities</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">There is plenty of car parking and places to secure a bike (bring your own lock).</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text/6 text-gray-600">There are two public toilet facilities near the starting line that may be open depending on nearby events. There is also a 24x7 fast food restaurant about 500m walk from the start line.</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text/6 text-gray-600">On the course, there are toilet blocks and drinking fountains after the 4km mark and near the 5km mark. There is also a drinking fountain in OTC park around the 2.4km mark.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="max-w-lg order-1 lg:order-2">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Course Description</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">The course is mostly on sealed (concrete/bitumen) tracks but there are two gravel sections and a dirt section that can be muddy after rain. The course consists of a small loop, a large loop and then an out and back section along part of the Rooty Hill parkrun course. It will be clearly marked on the day with erasable spray chalk that will fade after a week or two.</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text/6 text-gray-600">In the event of sustained rain leading up to the event, the dirt section after the 5km mark may become unsafe to pass. In that case, you will turn around at the 5km mark and return along the same route. The course markings will not be as clear in reverse so keep your eyes peeled for the arrows if you're navigationally challenged.</p>
          <!--After 500m, take the first left and head across the bridge over Eastern Creek towards the Bungarribee housing estate (Thomas Icely Ave). Turn left again and follow the path past the dam until you reach a road (Wirraga St, there'll be a large playground on your right). Turn right and do a large loop, keeping the road on your left as you zig zag back to Steeltrap Drive. Turn right onto Steeltrap Drive and then right again onto Hopkins Street near OTC Park. You'll finish the loop on Thomas Icely Avenue. Continue along the wide path, turning right where it narrows and crossing the wooden bridge to Bet Hyatt Avenue. Turn right again and keep the road on your left, following the wide path until just before Velocity Parade where you'll do a hairpin turn right, over Bungarribee Creek and towards the dog park. Veer left onto the gravel and then take the first right back onto the concrete path near Rooty Hill parkrun.-->
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8 lg:mt-0 ml-0 lg:mx-auto order-2 lg:order-1">
          <%= image_tag "bungarribee-route.png", class: "rounded-lg" %>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
    <div data-tabs-target="tab" id="tab-nepean" hidden>
      <h1 class="text-pretty text-4xl font-medium tracking-tighter text-gray-950 data-[dark]:text-white sm:text-6xl">Nepean River</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-2xl font-medium text-gray-500">Tench Reserve, Jamisontown</p>
      <div>
        <div class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-1 gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4">
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[#DB2955]">February 16</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">May 18</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">August 17</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">November 16</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <section class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="max-w-lg">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Course Start Point</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">The course starts and finishes in Tench Reserve, in the same area as Nepean River parkrun. If driving, there is parking on Tench Avenue and in carparks off Tench avenue.</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text-lg/6 text-gray-600"><a class="text-[#54494B] underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:no-underline hover:text-[#9DA39A]" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Nepean+River+Parkrun/@-33.7623863,150.6611338,17z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x6b1289ec090c8baf:0xa9d1ffa8acefca12!8m2!3d-33.7623908!4d150.6637087!16s%2Fg%2F11t9c9zkpm!5m1!1e1?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDEyNi4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D">Google Maps Link</a> | <a class="text-[#54494B] underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:no-underline hover:text-[#9DA39A]" href="https://maps.apple.com/?address=163%E2%80%93165%20Tench%20Ave%0APenrith%20NSW%202750%0AAustralia&auid=1916632410848447481&ll=-33.762531,150.663880&lsp=9902&q=Nepean%20River%20Parkrun&t=m">Apple Maps Link</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:row-span-2 mt-8 lg:my-auto">
          <%= image_tag "nepean-start.png", class: "rounded-lg" %>
        </div>
        <div class="max-lg:mt-8 lg:col-span-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Facilities</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">There is plenty of car parking and places to secure a bike (bring your own lock).</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text/6 text-gray-600">There are multiple public toilet facilities, both at the start/finish line and on the course but they may not open until the event has commenced. Multiple drinking fountains are available too.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="max-w-lg order-1 lg:order-2">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Course Description</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">The event is run entirely on sealed cycle/pedestrian paths that are well suited to pushing a pram and resistant to adverse weather. The course is an out and back course around the river. There are no road crossings but expect to encounter lots of runners and walkers along with some cyclists.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8 lg:mt-0 ml-0 lg:mx-auto order-2 lg:order-1">
          <%= image_tag "nepean-route.png", class: "rounded-lg" %>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
    <div data-tabs-target="tab" id="tab-parramatta" hidden>
      <h1 class="text-pretty text-4xl font-medium tracking-tighter text-gray-950 data-[dark]:text-white sm:text-6xl">Parramatta Park</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-2xl font-medium text-gray-500">Parramatta Park and Parramatta River</p>
      <div>
        <div class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-1 gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4">
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">March 16</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">June 15</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">September 21</div>
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white px-4 py-5 shadow sm:p-6">
            <div class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900">December 21</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <section class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="max-w-lg">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Course Start Point</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">Meet at the course finish point, near the Lady Fitzroy Memorial, just inside the old Tudorhouse Gates at George Street. After the pre-event briefing we'll move as a group to the start point near the Noller Footbridge.</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text-lg/6 text-gray-600"><a class="text-[#54494B] underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:no-underline hover:text-[#9DA39A]" href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Lady+Fitzroy+Memorial/@-33.8125395,150.9986062,19z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x6b12a33ae9a94bd1:0x4911e09a6c662c92!8m2!3d-33.8125742!4d150.9996972!16s%2Fg%2F11gwg61mh_!5m1!1e1?entry=ttu&g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDEyNi4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D">Google Maps Link</a> | <a class="text-[#54494B] underline underline-offset-[3px] hover:no-underline hover:text-[#9DA39A]" href="https://maps.apple.com/?address=O'Connell%20St,%20Parramatta%20NSW%202150,%20Australia&auid=755998292114138734&ll=-33.812575,150.999681&lsp=9902&q=Lady%20Mary%20Fitzroy&t=m">Apple Maps Link</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:row-span-2 mt-8 lg:my-auto">
          <%= image_tag "parramatta-start.png", class: "rounded-lg" %>
        </div>
        <div class="max-lg:mt-8 lg:col-span-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Facilities</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">There is usually plenty of parking within Parramatta Park and along the park
            road. Parking is also available in the council car park in O’Connell Street next to CommBank (Parramatta) Stadium. It is a short walk from the O’Connell Street car park to the meeting point via the Noller footbridge.</p>
          <p class="mt-8 text/6 text-gray-600">There are public toilet facilities, both at the start/finish line and on the course. Multiple drinking fountains are available around the course too.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="max-w-lg order-1 lg:order-2">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight">Course Description</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text/6 text-gray-600">The event is run entirely on sealed cycle/pedestrian paths that are well suited to pushing a pram and resistant to adverse weather. The course consists of three laps of the park loop, starting near the Noller Footbridge and finishing in front of the George Street gatehouse.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8 lg:mt-0 ml-0 lg:mx-auto order-2 lg:order-1">
          <%= image_tag "parramatta-route.png", class: "rounded-lg" %>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
